788
00:55:55,360 --> 00:55:57,490
What are you saying?

789
00:55:57,490 --> 00:55:59,890
Are you saying we should allow their relationship?

790
00:55:59,890 --> 00:56:02,040
What's wrong with that?

791
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:05,290
It's not something that bad.

792
00:56:05,290 --> 00:56:07,860
Chairman Lee has a lot of money, so why do you worry?

793
00:56:07,860 --> 00:56:11,520
I know you're concerned about the children, but money raises children these days.

794
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:14,010
They could study abroad later.

795
00:56:14,010 --> 00:56:19,730
To be honest, compared to a life of a struggle with someone her own age,

796
00:56:19,730 --> 00:56:24,040
it would be better for her to live comfortably married to Chairman Lee.

797
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:26,990
What's the big deal about a fourteen-year age difference?

798
00:56:26,990 --> 00:56:30,350
Couples with a twenty-year difference get married and live happily.

799
00:56:30,350 --> 00:56:32,440
He has three children, three!

800
00:56:32,440 --> 00:56:36,280
Do you want our twenty-seven years old Dan Dan raising the three children?

801
00:56:36,280 --> 00:56:40,890
Are you speaking carelessly because she's not your daughter?

802
00:56:40,890 --> 00:56:43,610
What did you just say?

803
00:56:43,610 --> 00:56:46,820
Is that how you've thought of me all this time?

804
00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:50,840
I spoke out of pity for Dan Dan. How can you say such a thing?

805
00:56:50,840 --> 00:56:54,610
I speak carelessly because she's not my daughter?

806
00:56:54,610 --> 00:56:57,770
Since Dan Dan was a baby,

807
00:56:57,770 --> 00:57:00,130
I changed her poopy diapers and raised her.

808
00:57:00,130 --> 00:57:03,990
I am saying this because I'm her mother!

809
00:57:03,990 --> 00:57:06,810
Rather than her having a hard life with someone her age,

810
00:57:06,810 --> 00:57:11,280
it's better for her to be with Chairman Lee, who she loves. How is that careless?

811
00:57:16,460 --> 00:57:19,700
You are driving me mad.

812
00:57:19,700 --> 00:57:24,000
Why do you speak to him like that when he's already upset?

813
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:26,500
I don't care! I feel better for saying what I wanted to.

814
00:57:26,500 --> 00:57:28,120
Did I say something wrong?

815
00:57:28,120 --> 00:57:30,840
I'm not scared of him anymore!

816
00:57:30,840 --> 00:57:34,320
Oh my, stop it.

817
00:57:43,540 --> 00:57:46,340
Hey, are you crazy?

818
00:57:46,340 --> 00:57:48,520
Do you want to screw me over?

819
00:57:48,520 --> 00:57:51,070
How can you bring an infant here!

820
00:57:51,070 --> 00:57:53,470
I'm sorry.

821
00:58:08,990 --> 00:58:14,690
I raised my Dan Dan with all my might.

822
00:58:30,470 --> 00:58:33,580
You said you have something to talk to me about.

823
00:58:35,720 --> 00:58:38,100
You...

824
00:58:40,230 --> 00:58:44,960
Take Dan Dan with you to the US.

825
00:58:44,960 --> 00:58:47,940
Soo Chul.

826
00:58:49,900 --> 00:58:52,640
Really?

827
00:58:52,640 --> 00:58:54,660
Are you sure I can do that?

828
00:58:54,660 --> 00:59:00,570
In return, you shall never reveal that you are her mother.

829
00:59:00,570 --> 00:59:02,830
Dan Dan knows her mother abandoned her.

830
00:59:02,830 --> 00:59:07,900
So if she finds out you are her mother, she will not go to the US with you.

831
00:59:07,900 --> 00:59:12,070
So no matter what, don't reveal it to her.

832
00:59:12,070 --> 00:59:15,260
Okay, I will do that.

833
00:59:15,260 --> 00:59:21,240
But since you are her mother, I'm trusting you to take good care of her.

834
00:59:21,240 --> 00:59:27,290
Make her forget Chairman Lee and begin a new life.

835
00:59:27,290 --> 00:59:30,580
Yes, Soo Chul. Do not worry.

836
00:59:30,580 --> 00:59:33,110
I will take good care of our daughter, Dan Dan.

837
00:59:33,110 --> 00:59:36,750
I will make her be a successful designer in the US.

838
00:59:36,750 --> 00:59:40,560
Thank you. Thank you very much.

839
00:59:40,560 --> 00:59:45,700
I'm not sending Dan Dan with you not because I approve of you or because I forgive you.

840
00:59:45,700 --> 00:59:47,850
Don't forget about that.

841
00:59:47,850 --> 00:59:51,160
I know.

842
00:59:51,160 --> 00:59:53,610
I know, of course.

843
01:00:04,070 --> 01:00:06,710
I'm sorry.

844
01:00:09,440 --> 01:00:12,290
I'm sorry...

845
01:00:23,990 --> 01:00:26,660
Yes.

846
01:00:26,660 --> 01:00:30,650
It's better to send her off to the US,

847
01:00:30,650 --> 01:00:33,540
than having her end up with a guy with three kids.

848
01:00:37,850 --> 01:00:40,170
Dan Dan.

849
01:00:46,110 --> 01:00:48,190
Here.

850
01:00:51,980 --> 01:00:55,730
I gave it some thought.

851
01:00:55,730 --> 01:01:00,230
I think the reason you keep getting swayed even after you said you would break up with Chairman Lee

852
01:01:00,230 --> 01:01:04,870
is that you're still physically close to him.

853
01:01:04,870 --> 01:01:07,330
To forget him, you have to be far away from him.

854
01:01:07,330 --> 01:01:13,240
Which is why, Dan Dan...

855
01:01:13,240 --> 01:01:18,190
Why don't you go to the US with CEO Anna next week?

856
01:01:18,190 --> 01:01:20,350
Dad?

857
01:01:20,350 --> 01:01:26,690
I met up with CEO Anna, and it just happened to be that the person who was supposed to go can't anymore.

858
01:01:26,690 --> 01:01:29,660
So I told her I'd let you go and she was very happy.

859
01:01:29,660 --> 01:01:31,120
Dad...

860
01:01:31,120 --> 01:01:35,720
You may think you're all grown up, Dan Dan.

861
01:01:35,720 --> 01:01:37,730
But you're still a kid in my eyes.

862
01:01:37,730 --> 01:01:39,890
You have never lived your own life properly yet.

863
01:01:39,890 --> 01:01:44,980
I can't watch you end up with Chairman Lee.

864
01:01:46,900 --> 01:01:53,300
You'll forget about Chairman Lee once you go to the US.

865
01:01:53,300 --> 01:01:58,400
Go and study more and do whatever you want to do.

866
01:01:58,400 --> 01:02:01,930
You said before that you wanted to study design.

867
01:02:01,930 --> 01:02:04,730
What better opportunity is there than this?

868
01:02:04,730 --> 01:02:06,880
Dad.

869
01:02:06,880 --> 01:02:10,210
I'm not saying you should settle down for good there.

870
01:02:10,210 --> 01:02:13,340
Just for three years,

871
01:02:13,340 --> 01:02:19,340
study a little more and live your own fantastic life like how other young folks do.

872
01:02:19,340 --> 01:02:22,690
Even after that, you think about Chairman Lee

873
01:02:22,690 --> 01:02:27,430
and can't forget him after all that.

874
01:02:27,430 --> 01:02:31,090
Then I'll reconsider about it.

875
01:02:31,090 --> 01:02:34,940
Do you really mean that?

876
01:02:34,940 --> 01:02:37,810
So then...

877
01:02:37,810 --> 01:02:41,910
If I say I still want to be with Chairman after three years,

878
01:02:41,910 --> 01:02:46,170
will you really think about allowing us?

879
01:02:46,170 --> 01:02:49,960
Yes. I will do that.

880
01:02:49,960 --> 01:02:54,830
So try living there for just three years for now.

881
01:02:54,830 --> 01:03:01,210
Dan Dan. This is my last wish.

882
01:03:06,610 --> 01:03:09,860
All right, Dad.

883
01:03:09,860 --> 01:03:12,780
I will do that.

884
01:03:15,250 --> 01:03:18,070
Thank you, Dan Dan.

885
01:03:18,070 --> 01:03:20,410
Thank you.

886
01:03:28,990 --> 01:03:32,230
Young Gook.

887
01:03:32,230 --> 01:03:36,380
I heard that you broke up with Ms. Park.

888
01:03:36,380 --> 01:03:39,060
You made the right choice.

889
01:03:40,600 --> 01:03:43,790
Noona.

890
01:03:43,790 --> 01:03:48,440
Is that what you came to talk about?

891
01:03:48,440 --> 01:03:55,390
Well, the truth is, Ms. Park's father, Driver Park,

892
01:03:55,390 --> 01:03:58,240
came by to see me.

893
01:03:58,240 --> 01:04:03,960
He pleaded to me to take Ms. Park to the US with me, so I said I will.

894
01:04:03,960 --> 01:04:07,770
Ms. Park was supposed to work with me anyway.

895
01:04:07,770 --> 01:04:13,610
I came here today because I thought you should know too.

896
01:04:13,610 --> 01:04:16,050
Okay. I understand.

897
01:04:16,050 --> 01:04:22,980
Now that everything has come to this end, you should move on too, Young Gook.

898
01:04:22,980 --> 01:04:25,290
Don't worry.

899
01:04:25,290 --> 01:04:30,710
Ms. Park and I decided to end things.

900
01:04:30,710 --> 01:04:34,040
All right. Thank you, Young Gook.

901
01:04:34,040 --> 01:04:37,770
But, Noona.

902
01:04:37,770 --> 01:04:46,780
Why would you thank me for breaking up with Ms. Park?

903
01:04:46,780 --> 01:04:51,700
Well, you see...

904
01:04:51,700 --> 01:04:55,940
The two of you aren't a good match.

905
01:04:55,940 --> 01:05:01,050
You also got an opportunity to meet a better person.

906
01:05:01,050 --> 01:05:03,410
That's why I said it.

907
01:05:05,200 --> 01:05:07,950
Noona.

908
01:05:07,950 --> 01:05:11,280
You have loved someone before too.

909
01:05:11,280 --> 01:05:17,980
You know well how hard it is when you break up with that someone.

910
01:05:17,980 --> 01:05:20,710
Honestly, I'm struggling right now.

911
01:05:20,710 --> 01:05:23,970
I didn't break up with Ms. Park because I wanted to.

912
01:05:23,970 --> 01:05:29,980
I only broke up because I put myself in Driver Park's shoes as someone who has a daughter also.

913
01:05:29,980 --> 01:05:34,150
But for you to do this to me makes me feel awful.

914
01:05:34,150 --> 01:05:37,200
You don't seem like the Ji Young Noona I knew.

915
01:05:37,200 --> 01:05:42,730
I thought you would take my side no matter what the situation.

916
01:05:42,730 --> 01:05:47,800
All right, Young Gook. I'm sorry about that too.

917
01:05:47,800 --> 01:05:50,570
The fact that that's all I can say to you.

918
01:05:50,570 --> 01:05:55,560
But this is all for your sake.

919
01:05:55,560 --> 01:05:58,370
What?

920
01:05:58,370 --> 01:06:03,470
This is all for my sake? How so?

921
01:06:03,470 --> 01:06:07,490
If it was for my sake, you should be rooting for our love.

922
01:06:07,490 --> 01:06:13,870
I'm hurting this much from breaking up with Ms. Park. But you're saying this is all for my sake?

923
01:06:13,870 --> 01:06:18,390
Noona. I have something to ask you too.

924
01:06:18,390 --> 01:06:23,090
Fine. I understand Driver Park not agreeing to our relationship.

925
01:06:23,090 --> 01:06:25,610
I fully understand how he feels.

926
01:06:25,610 --> 01:06:30,300
But why are you so against our relationship to this extent, Noona?

927
01:06:31,900 --> 01:06:35,330
Young Gook.

928
01:06:35,330 --> 01:06:37,240
You see...

929
01:06:37,240 --> 01:06:40,890
It's because I'm worried people will point fingers at you.

930
01:06:40,890 --> 01:06:43,170
I'm truly worried for you.

931
01:06:43,170 --> 01:06:48,820
Noona. I beg you...

932
01:06:48,820 --> 01:06:53,410
But don't ever say it's for my sake again.

933
01:06:53,410 --> 01:06:56,540
I have a meeting.

934
01:06:59,300 --> 01:07:03,550
All right. I got it.

935
01:07:03,550 --> 01:07:06,570
I'll get going.

936
01:07:24,030 --> 01:07:29,500
Chairman. I decided to go to the US.

937
01:07:29,500 --> 01:07:34,290
I know. I heard from CEO Anna.

938
01:07:34,290 --> 01:07:39,850
Chairman. Can you wait for me?

939
01:07:39,850 --> 01:07:43,100
I'm going so that I can see you again.

940
01:07:43,100 --> 01:07:46,290
My dad told me to try living three years in the US.

941
01:07:46,290 --> 01:07:48,320
But if I still can't forget about you,

942
01:07:48,320 --> 01:07:52,400
then he said he would reconsider our relationship.

943
01:07:52,400 --> 01:07:57,570
I'll be well in the US and come back.

944
01:07:57,570 --> 01:08:02,290
So you can't forget me, Chairman, okay?

945
01:08:02,290 --> 01:08:04,000
Okay.

946
01:08:04,000 --> 01:08:07,040
Then I will wait for you this time.

947
01:08:07,040 --> 01:08:11,110
So you go and don't think about me.

948
01:08:11,110 --> 01:08:15,810
Study more and do everything you want to do.

949
01:08:15,810 --> 01:08:19,730
And if you meet a good person, you should date.

950
01:08:19,730 --> 01:08:23,590
Chairman! Don't say stuff like that.

951
01:08:23,590 --> 01:08:28,900
I'm going to come back after three years. I will!

952
01:08:52,790 --> 01:08:55,520
[FT Group]

953
01:08:55,520 --> 01:09:02,980
[Fantom]

954
01:09:02,980 --> 01:09:03,930
Yes?

955
01:09:03,930 --> 01:09:08,310
Park Dan Dan's biological mother that you requested before, I found her.

956
01:09:08,310 --> 01:09:09,680
Is that so?

957
01:09:09,680 --> 01:09:14,780
Park Dan Dan's biological mother's name is Kim Ji Young.

958
01:09:14,780 --> 01:09:18,670
Kim Ji Young?

959
01:09:25,870 --> 01:09:33,390
♫ Why do you run away, love like a shy child ♫

960
01:09:33,390 --> 01:09:40,060
♫ In case I lose it, I hold it tight ♫

961
01:09:40,060 --> 01:09:47,290
♫ But love always runs away, chased by longing ♫

962
01:09:47,290 --> 01:09:53,970
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

963
01:09:53,970 --> 01:10:01,890
♫ I have to abandon the longing and the grieves ♫

964
01:10:01,890 --> 01:10:08,050
♫ What am I looking for on this road wandering ♫

965
01:10:08,050 --> 01:10:10,910
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

966
01:10:10,910 --> 01:10:12,950
She'll finish her work within this week.

967
01:10:12,950 --> 01:10:15,360
Hurry up with her preparations for leaving. And don't forget what I said to you.

968
01:10:15,360 --> 01:10:18,080
I won't let her know I'm her mom until the day she dies.

969
01:10:18,080 --> 01:10:20,450
Those two are meeting again.

970
01:10:20,450 --> 01:10:22,910
This is CEO Anna Kim and my Soo Chul.

971
01:10:22,910 --> 01:10:24,970
Are you saying these two are having an affair?

972
01:10:24,970 --> 01:10:26,700
Where is our son, Sarah?

973
01:10:26,700 --> 01:10:29,390
Let's find our son so the three of us can start over again.

974
01:10:29,390 --> 01:10:32,650
- Do you have a death wish?
- Oh, no!

975
01:10:32,650 --> 01:10:34,070
Do you want to go on a farewell trip?

976
01:10:34,070 --> 01:10:35,550
We can't just say goodbye like this.

977
01:10:35,550 --> 01:10:37,510
I am going to return no matter what.

978
01:10:37,510 --> 01:10:39,110
Let's make sure to meet again.

979
01:10:39,110 --> 01:10:41,040
Be happy, Ms. Park.

980
01:10:41,040 --> 01:10:44,870
She was going to take my Soo Chul to the US.

981
01:10:44,870 --> 01:10:46,440
Please take this, Soo Chul.

982
01:10:46,440 --> 01:10:49,190
Didn't I tell you? Never to reveal you're her mother.

983
01:10:49,190 --> 01:10:51,860
What do you mean she's Dan Dan's mother?

984
01:10:51,860 --> 01:10:54,120
What are you saying?

985
01:10:54,120 --> 01:10:55,480
♫ What am I looking for  ♫
